            <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2 flex items-center">
              <i class="material-icons mr-2 text-blue-600">free_breakfast</i>
              Free for Everyone
            </h4>
            <p class="text-blue-800 text-sm">
              Universes are completely free on Notebook.ai! Every user gets <strong>5 free universes</strong> to organize their worldbuilding projects.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Getting Started -->
        <section id="getting-started" class="mb-12">
          <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-400 p-6 rounded-r-lg mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-900 mb-4 flex items-center">
              <i class="material-icons mr-3 text-green-600">rocket_launch</i>
              Getting Started
            </h2>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Creating Your First Universe</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            To create your first universe:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-6 ml-4">
            <li>Navigate to your <strong>Universe</strong> section in the sidebar</li>
            <li>Click the <strong>"Create New Universe"</strong> button</li>
            <li>Give your universe a descriptive name</li>
            <li>Add a description explaining the world you're building</li>
            <li>Set additional details like genre, magic system, and technology level</li>
          </ol>

          <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-yellow-900 mb-2 flex items-center">
              <i class="material-icons mr-2 text-yellow-600">lightbulb</i>
              Pro Tip
            </h4>
            <p class="text-yellow-800 text-sm">
              Start with a clear, memorable name for your universe. This will help you stay organized as you create more worlds and switch between them.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Understanding Your Limits</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Free accounts include 5 universes, which is perfect for most worldbuilders. You can have:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-gray-700 mb-6 ml-4">
            <li>Multiple stories set in the same universe</li>
            <li>Different time periods within the same world</li>
            <li>Separate experimental or alternative version worlds</li>
            <li>Collaborative universes shared with friends</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Adding Content to Universes -->
        <section id="adding-content" class="mb-12">
          <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-6 rounded-r-lg mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-4 flex items-center">
              <i class="material-icons mr-3 text-blue-600">add_circle</i>
              Adding Content to Universes
            </h2>
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Every page you create in Notebook.ai can optionally belong to a universe. This includes:
